<% /* "Embed item" control (audio/video). Single source of truth — included by the
      media card of the standard, grid, and timeline item forms. On add/edit media
      forms the *.common.* form modules relocate #embed-item-group up next to the
      Pop-up Window Description label and disable that description while this box is
      checked, because embedded items do not open the pop-up viewer. */ %>
<div id="embed-item-group" class="form-group" style="padding-top: 10px">
    <small class="form-text text-muted"><i class="fa fa-exclamation-circle" aria-hidden="true"></i> <em>Embedded items do not open the item viewer (pop-up window)</em></small>
    <label for="embed-item" style="font-weight: normal; cursor: pointer">Embed item&nbsp;<input type="checkbox" id="embed-item" name="embed_item"></label>
</div>
